text: Rowena is an unincorporated community in Redwood County, in the U.S. state of Minnesota. ==History== Rowena was laid out in 1902. The community was named after the character Lady Rowena from Walter Scott's novel Ivanhoe. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Redwood County, Minnesota Category:Unincorporated communities in Minnesota
title: Rowena, Minnesota
